    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>OFF-YEAR TESTS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Debra Nussbaum</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Nussbaum, Debra</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Public school districts in Newark and Paterson, NJ, are developing their own standardized tests to help students prepare for state proficiency assessment exams (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Newark and Paterson public school districts are formulating their own standardized tests for students -- which it will begin giving during the 2000-2001 school year -- to help prepare them for the New Jersey state proficiency assessment tests the following year. The tests, will be given to students in grades 3, 7 and 10 next spring. Students take the state tests in grades 4, 8 and 11.</p>
        <p>Debra Nussbaum</p>
      </block>
